goals.question: What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of fertility vs life_expect
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is any relationship between fertility and life expectancy. If there is a negative correlation, it could indicate that countries with higher fertility rates have lower life expectancies.

goals.question: What is the distribution of fertility rates across different countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of fertility rates across different countries. It could help identify countries with high or low fertility rates.

goals.question: What is the distribution of life expectancies across different countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of life expectancies across different countries. It could help identify countries with high or low life expectancies.

goals.question: How does the fertility rate vary over time for different countries?
goals.visualization: line chart of fertility vs year for each country
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the trend of fertility rates over time for different countries. It could help identify countries where fertility rates are increasing or decreasing.

goals.question: How does the life expectancy vary over time for different countries?
goals.visualization: line chart of life_expect vs year for each country
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the trend of life expectancies over time for different countries. It could help identify countries where life expectancies are increasing or decreasing.

code:
```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['fertility', 'life_expect']]
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='fertility', y='life_expect')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='fertility', color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean fertility rate: {:.2f}'.format(data['fertility'].mean()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.xlabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility rates across different countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['life_expect']]
    sns.histplot(data, x='life_expect', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['life_expect'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['life_expect'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancies across different countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='fertility', hue='country', data=data, legend='full')
    plt.title('How does the fertility rate vary over time for different countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['year', 'life_expect', 'country']]
    data = data.dropna()
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by=['year'])
    sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(15,10)})
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='life_expect', hue='country', data=data, palette='bright')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('How does the life expectancy vary over time for different countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
